 previously recognized limits and build a future that was not merely a recuperation of the past, but fundamentally different from it. A theoretically inflected work combining intellectual history and the history of science, this book will appeal to anyone interested in European history and the history of science, as well as the history of France, the Enlightenment, and the French Revolution.  afunded by University of Toronto Libraries  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnlightenmentxInfluencezFrance. 0aEnlightenmentzFrancexInfluence. 0aEnlightenmentzFrance. 0aForecastingxSocial aspectsxHistoryy18th centuryzFrance. 0aForecastingxSocial aspectszFrancexHistoryy18th century. 0aFuture, ThexPhilosophy. 0aFuture, ThexSocial aspectsxHistoryy18th centuryzFrance. 0aFuture, ThexSocial aspectszFrancexHistoryy18th century. 0aPhilosophy, Frenchy18th century. 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh  aEnlightenment philosophy.  aEuropean history.  aFrance.  aFrench Revolution.  aYear One.  aenlightenment.  afuturism.  ahistory of science.  ahistory of technology.  ahistory of time.  aideas of the future.  aphilosophy.2 aUniversity of Toronto Librariesefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781487541408zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487541408zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487541408/original  a978-3-11-069045-3 University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA